{"about_the_game":"Unanimy starts as a simple puzzle game about getting a collection of robots to the same tile, while all of them move in sync. Throughout the game's six worlds, the mechanics become more and more complicated.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel0.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>We start with the basic task of getting our two robots together. They move in sync, you can use the walls to stop them, and if any fall off, you fail the level and must either restart or undo your last move.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel1.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Later, we see colored walls. Blue robots are blocked by blue walls, and red robots are blocked by red walls.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel2.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Then we add reversed robots. Notice the brighter tone and the inverted colors on the arrows, indicating that when most robots would move right, these will move left.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel3.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Eventually, we add green robots. Unlike red and blue which can't fall off or you fail the level, green robots <i>must</i> fall off for the level to be complete.<br><br>All the while, you'll be not only solving each level, but optimizing your solutions through the <i>par</i> mechanic, which gives you an added goal on <i>every</i> level to complete it in as few moves as possible!","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1657755840","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/page_bg_generated.jpg?t=1657755840","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1657755840","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1657755840","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Steam Achievements","id":22},{"description":"Includes level editor","id":17}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"detailed_description":"Unanimy starts as a simple puzzle game about getting a collection of robots to the same tile, while all of them move in sync. Throughout the game's six worlds, the mechanics become more and more complicated.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel0.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>We start with the basic task of getting our two robots together. They move in sync, you can use the walls to stop them, and if any fall off, you fail the level and must either restart or undo your last move.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel1.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Later, we see colored walls. Blue robots are blocked by blue walls, and red robots are blocked by red walls.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel2.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Then we add reversed robots. Notice the brighter tone and the inverted colors on the arrows, indicating that when most robots would move right, these will move left.<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/extras/sampleLevel3.gif?t=1657755840\" /><br>Eventually, we add green robots. Unlike red and blue which can't fall off or you fail the level, green robots <i>must</i> fall off for the level to be complete.<br><br>All the while, you'll be not only solving each level, but optimizing your solutions through the <i>par</i> mechanic, which gives you an added goal on <i>every</i> level to complete it in as few moves as possible!","developers":["ComputerCow"],"genres":[{"description":"Indie","id":"23"},{"description":"Strategy","id":"2"}],"header_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2077860/header.jpg?t=1657755840","is_free":false,"linux_requirements":[],"mac_requirements":[],"movies":[{"highlight":true,"id":256894766,"mp4":{"480":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256894766/movie480.mp4?t=1657208262","max":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256894766/movie_max.mp4?t=1657208262"},"name":"This Can Get So Much More Complicated","thumbnail":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/256894766/movie.293x165.jpg?t=1657208262","webm":{"480":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256894766/movie480_vp9.webm?t=1657208262","max":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256894766/movie_max_vp9.webm?t=1657208262"}},{"highlight":true,"id":256896244,"mp4":{"480":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256896244/movie480.mp4?t=1657755839","max":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256896244/movie_max.mp4?t=1657755839"},"name":"Par","thumbnail":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/256896244/movie.293x165.jpg?t=1657755839","webm":{"480":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256896244/movie480_vp9.webm?t=1657755839","max":"http://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/256896244/movie_max_vp9.webm?t=1657755839"}}],"name":"Unanimy","package_groups":[],"pc_requirements":{"minimum":"<strong>Minimum:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Intel i5 or equivalent<br></li><li><strong>Memory:</strong> 5 GB RAM<br></li><li><strong>Graphics:</strong> Intel Iris Xe Graphics or better<br></li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 300 MB available space<br></li><li><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> (not thoroughl